Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In the past 24 hours, the USA (110 714), India (43 174), Brazil (37 672), and Turkey (36 008) have reported the highest numbers of cases. A global total of 10 901 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (25-26 Nov 2020).

Countries reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (13 countries) include the USA, India, Brazil, Turkey, Italy (29 001), Russia (25 487), Germany (21 576), UK (17 555), Poland (16 690), Ukraine (15 331), Spain (15 212), Iran (13 961), and France (13 563). A total of 64 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 34 of the 64 countries reporting more than 1000 newly confirmed cases are from the European region, 12 are from the Americas region, 9 are from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 5 are from the South East Asia region, 2 are from the Western Pacific region, and 2 are from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have decreased by 1.7%, while daily reported deaths have increased by 9.0%. Recognizing that 26 Nov 2020 was a national holiday in the USA, with a 4-day weekend usually observed and inherent in this a decrease in reporting -- 23 of 62 reporting units reported 0 cases today (26 Nov 2020), the 7-day averages for newly confirmed cases are decreased by 1.6% and the daily reported deaths are increased by 15.1%.

Impression: The global daily reported cases seem to be leveling off although the absolute case counts continue to be high on a daily basis. Countries in the European and the Americas regions are still showing the largest increases in daily new case counts, followed by the Eastern Mediterranean and the South East Asia regions. The USA continues to show uncontrolled transmission. South Korea continues to report more than 500 cases per day. Germany has crossed the 1 million cumulative case mark, with 12 countries reporting more than 1 million cases. - Mod.MPP]
